snippet.textDisplay:
I have over 250TB's of data on my server. Have fun doing backups or transferring even a small percent of that over gigabit. Especially if multiple people are hitting hard it at the same time.....
40Gb/s infiniband connection server to switch then 10Gb Cat.6a out to most of the clients. Never have any hiccups even when multiple users are playing 4k content unlike on our old gigabit LAN.
Do most people need this? No. But saying there is no point is demonstrably false.
